HEADWORD: Anticathode
<hw>An`ti*cath"ode</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Phys.)</fld>
<def>The part of a vacuum tube opposite the cathode. Upon it the cathode
rays impinge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

